post_text: We are aware of Governor DeWine’s announcement to close schools through April 3rd. Following the Governor’s guidance, we will be closed as well. We will continue to post updates as they come.

post_text: Good morning families, we are continuing to monitor the coronavirus situation and make adjustments in the best interest of student and staff safety. To help prevent the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19), we are cancelling all scheduled field trips and prohibiting spectator participation at extra-curricular events. If you have specific questions about an event, feel free to call the school or email the front office. Thank you for your understanding. We will continue to post updates as they come.

post_text: I know many are concerned about the Coronavirus (COVID-19) and have been asking about the plans for our school. Our staff is working with our school officials to coordinate efforts and ensure the safety of our staff and students with minimal disruption to effective instruction and school operation. Visit our website or facebook page for the most up to date information.
